Package: mCanonicalTockySeq
Title: Multidimensional Canonical Tocky Analysis of Temporal and Developmental Structure in Single-Cell Transcriptomes
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Masahiro", "Ono", email = "monotockylab@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID="0000-0002-9284-7326"))
Description: Implements methods for analysing single-cell RNA-seq data in systems where temporal and developmental progression are recorded simultaneously. The package constructs a biologically anchored canonical space from Tocky and developmental landmark populations, supports extraction of continuous Tocky manifolds, developmental fate scoring, gene-centric trajectory analysis, and projection of new datasets into an established reference space.
Depends: R (>= 4.2.0)
Imports: MASS, dplyr, ggplot2, patchwork, plotly, scales, shiny, BiocParallel, irlba, Matrix, pheatmap, tradeSeq, Seurat, methods, utils, rlang
